---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="About — AI Project Standard" description="About the AI Project Standard, its architecture, and its maintainer.">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">About</h1>

  <section class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-4">
    <p class="max-w-3xl">
      A starting baseline for open-source projects that use AI. Four pillars — human-AI collaboration,
      open-source operations, software engineering, knowledge and documentation. Three adoption
      profiles. Five common adoption paths.
    </p>
    <p class="max-w-3xl">
      The repository is the operational layer: workflows, AI state, governance, templates. This site
      is the knowledge layer: explanations, comparisons, tutorials, research, blog.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-12 flex flex-col gap-3">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Maintainer</h2>
    <p>
      Created and maintained by <a href="https://github.com/rubennati">Ruben Nati</a>. Contributions
      welcome — see the
      <a href="https://github.com/rubennati/ai-project-standard/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md">contribution guide</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 flex flex-col gap-3">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">License</h2>
    <p>
      Released under the MIT License. See the
      <a href="https://github.com/rubennati/ai-project-standard/blob/main/LICENSE">LICENSE</a> file.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 flex flex-col gap-3">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Acknowledgements</h2>
    <p>
      The standard draws on the <code>AGENTS.md</code> cross-vendor convention popularised by the
      Codex CLI, GitHub Copilot's instructions file, Cursor's MDC rules format, and the wider
      open-source community's work on contribution and governance baselines.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
